title: For Sale/Trade:  Kel-Tec RFB
postcontent: I know what you're thinking: a Kel-Tec product? I felt the same way, trust me. But evidently this is one of the few Kel-Tec products that's not a cheap hunk of crap (the other being this rifle's younger 5.56mm brother, the RDB), and it definitely feels and shoots solidly and reliably. Brand new condition Kel-Tec RFB. I took it to the mountains once to zero it at 100 yards, fired 38 total M80 spec rounds from 5 different magazines to ensure reliability--there weren't any failures. Have to sell it because I'm going with another FAL instead and I'm a FAL fanboy. The RFB is a really nice-handling bullpup that's extremely pointable. There's complaints about recoil but compared to other 308 battle rifles I've fired the only more easier shooting one is the SCAR. These rifles are very easy to accessorize and upgrade if that's your thing.  Comes with one Thermold repair kit, ask about other FAL repair kits as well. Price is firm.
